<doc id="7361" url="https://en.wikinews.org/wiki?curid=7361" title="University of North Carolina wins 2005 basketball tournament">
<h1>University of North Carolina wins 2005 basketball tournament</h1>
♡❤♡April 7, 2005♡❤♡

The &lt;a href="w%3AUniversity%20of%20North%20Carolina"&gt;University of North Carolina&lt;/a&gt; Tar Heels won the 2005 &lt;a href="w%3ANCAA"&gt;National Collegiate Athletic Association&lt;/a&gt; (NCAA) Division I Men's Basketball Championship Title in the U.S. National college Basketball tournament, beating the &lt;a href="w%3AUniversity%20of%20Illinois"&gt;University of Illinois&lt;/a&gt; Fighting Illini by 75 points to 70. This tournament is sometimes referred to as &lt;a href="w%3AMarch%20Madness"&gt;March Madness&lt;/a&gt;. The final championship game was played on the evening of April 4, 2005 at the &lt;a href="w%3AEdward%20Jones%20Dome"&gt;Edward Jones Dome&lt;/a&gt; in St. Louis, Missouri. 

