BULLET::::- William W. Beck, Jr.. "&lt;a href="http%3A//www2.townonline.com/cambridge/opinion/view.bg%3Farticleid%3D210080"&gt;Beck: Oversight of Grace site is not ending&lt;/a&gt;" — &lt;i&gt;&lt;span class="interwiki-link-foreign"&gt;&lt;a href="w%3AThe%20Cambridge%20Chronicle"&gt;The Cambridge Chronicle&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/i&gt;, March 24, 2005
BULLET::::- Sarah Andrews. "&lt;a href="http%3A//www2.townonline.com/cambridge/localRegional/view.bg%3Farticleid%3D195933"&gt;Grace neighbors don't want to police site&lt;/a&gt;" — &lt;i&gt;&lt;span class="interwiki-link-foreign"&gt;&lt;a href="w%3AThe%20Cambridge%20Chronicle"&gt;The Cambridge Chronicle&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/i&gt;, March 3, 2005
BULLET::::- "&lt;a href="http%3A//www.usdoj.gov/opa/pr/2005/February/05_enrd_048.htm"&gt;W.R. GRACE AND EXECUTIVES CHARGED WITH FRAUD, OBSTRUCTION OF JUSTICE, AND ENDANGERING LIBBY, MONTANA COMMUNITY&lt;/a&gt;" — &lt;i&gt;&lt;span class="interwiki-link-foreign"&gt;&lt;a href="w%3AUS%20Department%20of%20Justice%20website"&gt;US Department of Justice website&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/i&gt;, February 7, 2005

</ul>


