BULLET::::- Nick Alexander. "&lt;a href="http%3A//www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/main.jhtml%3Fxml%3D/sport/2005/04/17/srcrok17.xml%26amp%3BsSheet%3D/sport/2005/04/17/ixrugu.html"&gt;Croke Park gets rugby and soccer&lt;/a&gt;" — &lt;i&gt;&lt;span class="interwiki-link-foreign"&gt;&lt;a href="w%3AThe%20Telegraph"&gt;The Telegraph&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/i&gt;, April 17, 2005
BULLET::::- "&lt;a href="http%3A//news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/northern_ireland/gaelic_games/4452449.stm"&gt;Croke Park opened to other sports&lt;/a&gt;" — &lt;i&gt;&lt;span class="interwiki-link-foreign"&gt;&lt;a href="w%3ABBC%20News"&gt;BBC News&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/i&gt;, April 16, 2005
BULLET::::- "&lt;a href="http%3A//today.reuters.co.uk/news/newsArticle.aspx%3Ftype%3DrugbyNews%26amp%3BstoryID%3DURI%3Aurn%3Anewsml%3Areuters.com%3A20050416%3AMTFH45886_2005-04-16_16-38-56_L11411105%3A1"&gt;Ireland's GAA votes to open up Croke Park&lt;/a&gt;" — &lt;i&gt;&lt;span class="interwiki-link-foreign"&gt;&lt;a href="w%3AReuters"&gt;Reuters&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/i&gt;, April 16, 2005

